# Static archive of GameCon 2005 (reconstructed from the Internet Archive).
#
# The 2005 festival ran 7.-10. 7. 2005 in OLOMOUC (DDM, tř. 17. listopadu 47 +
# nearby university dorms). It was still run by the Altar publishing house, and
# in 2005 GameCon was a SECTION of the whole altar.cz publisher site (path
# altar.cz/gamecon/), not a standalone site or subdomain — older than the
# gamecon.altar.cz era (2006-2008).
#
# Scope: the GameCon pages (~29 /gamecon/ pages, incl. the Mistrovství v DrD
# results archive vysledky95..vysledky04) served at the root, PLUS the Altar
# publisher-site nav menu it links to — the section landing pages (/altar/*,
# /arena/, /battletech/, /drd/, /drdplus/, /dech/, /hexaedr/, /akce/, /prog/,
# /odkazy/, /kontakt/, plus the altar.cz path pages /proroctvi/, /risesnu/) and
# one level deeper. The original /gamecon/ link prefix was rewritten to /. All
# restored from web.archive.org in the 2005 capture window (so the publisher
# content matches the year), transcoded WINDOWS-1250 -> UTF-8.
#
# Still out of scope (themed 404): dynamic CGI (/cgi/search.cgi, /cgi/doc/*),
# the product catalog, and links deeper than one level — incl. /altar/index.html
# and /help/informace.html, which weren't captured in the 2005 window. (The
# /cgi/doc DrD rules tree was reconstructed only for the 2003 archive.)
#
# Assets (stylesheets/default.css, img/gamecon/*) are served at their original
# absolute paths, since the pages reference them absolutely.

DirectoryIndex index.html
ErrorDocument 404 /404.html

<IfModule mod_rewrite.c>
    RewriteEngine On

    # Serve real files / dirs directly (pages at root, assets under their paths).
    RewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME} -f [OR]
    RewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME} -d
    RewriteRule ^ - [L]

    # Homepage.
    RewriteRule ^$  index.html [L]

    # Everything else (cross-site Altar chrome, uncaptured) -> themed 404.
    RewriteRule ^.*$ - [R=404,L]
</IfModule>
